text: Robert Archbold (died 26 February 1855) was an Irish Whig politician. Archbold was first elected Whig MP for at the 1837 general election and held the seat until 1847 when he did not seek re-election. ==References== ==External links== * Category:UK MPs 1837–1841 Category:UK MPs 1841–1847 Category:Whig (British political party) MPs for Irish constituencies Category:1855 deaths
